{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3499427,"name":"","username":"Popcorn","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/popcorn/{size}/219298_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-01T23:03:05.874Z","cooked":"<p>Our robot is driving correctly in tele-op, but in autonomous, the starting pose doesn’t seem to be set correctly, and the change in estimated field-relative pose often doesn’t match the robot-relative speed commanded. All test pictures were run on a cart with no <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> for now because the robot’s estimated pose is incorrect to begin with.</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/1/b/1bace3d207fce4976bfc0b27bd04cd59c04e1123.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/1bace3d207fce4976bfc0b27bd04cd59c04e1123" title="Screenshot from 2025-02-01 14-12-57"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/1/b/1bace3d207fce4976bfc0b27bd04cd59c04e1123_2_690x336.png" alt="Screenshot from 2025-02-01 14-12-57" data-base62-sha1="3WPj0MtVIMm7AhTZgoCEaKTPHEL" width="690" height="336" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/1/b/1bace3d207fce4976bfc0b27bd04cd59c04e1123_2_690x336.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/1/b/1bace3d207fce4976bfc0b27bd04cd59c04e1123_2_1035x504.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/1/b/1bace3d207fce4976bfc0b27bd04cd59c04e1123.png 2x" data-dominant-color="1E252E"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">Screenshot from 2025-02-01 14-12-57</span><span class="informations">1205×587 63.1 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>Here, we want our starting rotation to be 0, but Pathplanner tries to set the rotation to 180 (as seen by the ghost). However, the robot does follow the (incorrect) generated trajectory correctly.</p>
<p>Here is what the path should look like:</p>
<p><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/7/1/7183b671a12c3b456c3c6e174d91877c93c688a6.gif" alt="Test - Line" data-base62-sha1="gcc983Cvkofba2PtaFlOFoQiXAi" width="690" height="316" class="animated"></p>
<p>Are we not setting the starting pose correctly in the GUI? I’m not sure where the 180 starting rotation that is actually set is coming from, but it may have something to do with the path heading/us not actually setting the starting pose in GUI (when we change this path’s heading to 0 from 180, Pathplanner will then try to set the robot’s rotation to 0).</p>
<p>However, the gyroscope is actually never reset and stays at 180 whether Pathplanner tries to set 0 or 180.</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/b/d/bd53e9bc8dfa26288780466e80feeb531297418c.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/bd53e9bc8dfa26288780466e80feeb531297418c" title="Screenshot from 2025-02-01 14-18-39"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/b/d/bd53e9bc8dfa26288780466e80feeb531297418c_2_690x364.png" alt="Screenshot from 2025-02-01 14-18-39" data-base62-sha1="r0S1xaVJbX5FnuhRzypVZb3SEFu" width="690" height="364" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/b/d/bd53e9bc8dfa26288780466e80feeb531297418c_2_690x364.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/b/d/bd53e9bc8dfa26288780466e80feeb531297418c_2_1035x546.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/b/d/bd53e9bc8dfa26288780466e80feeb531297418c_2_1380x728.png 2x" data-dominant-color="1D1D23"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">Screenshot from 2025-02-01 14-18-39</span><span class="informations">1895×1000 202 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>This is another path that is also supposed to start with a rotation of 0 but moves in the +X direction instead of -X. As seen by the ghost, Pathplanner generates the correct starting position (maybe has to do with the heading also being 0 instead of 180?) but the robot follows the path incorrectly.</p>
<p><div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/4/c/4ce87ff60ce7bd607bbdba4580cbd9bdba933a99.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/4ce87ff60ce7bd607bbdba4580cbd9bdba933a99" title="More Complex Path, Incorrect Starting Pose, Incorrect Path Following"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/4/c/4ce87ff60ce7bd607bbdba4580cbd9bdba933a99_2_690x364.png" alt="More Complex Path, Incorrect Starting Pose, Incorrect Path Following" data-base62-sha1="aYmpOzn7I3FhuKUFYdfR9piJk81" width="690" height="364" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/4/c/4ce87ff60ce7bd607bbdba4580cbd9bdba933a99_2_690x364.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/4/c/4ce87ff60ce7bd607bbdba4580cbd9bdba933a99_2_1035x546.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/4/c/4ce87ff60ce7bd607bbdba4580cbd9bdba933a99_2_1380x728.png 2x" data-dominant-color="1E1D23"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">More Complex Path, Incorrect Starting Pose, Incorrect Path Following</span><span class="informations">1895×1000 225 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>As shown by this path, since the starting position isn’t what it should be, the robot drives exactly inverted of the actual path.</p>
<p>Here are things we’ve tried to do to fix it and the results:</p>
<ul>
<li>Confirmed swerve IDs, drive inversion, angle inversion, angle offsets, CANcoder vs. angle motor phase, gyroscope inversion: no obvious issues</li>
<li>Tried setting gyro yaw multiple times directly at the start of auto: gives robot correct rotation and starting pose and drives path correctly (without PIDs). However, pose changes in opposite direction of actual driving (ex: robot goes +X in real life but estimated pose goes -X; behaves correctly in tele-op)</li>
</ul>
<p>Here is the code to reset the pose that Pathplanner’s AutoBuilder calls:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">void SwerveDrive::SetPose(frc::Pose2d pose, bool justRotation) {
    UpdateEstimator();
    if (justRotation) {
        auto currentPose = GetEstimatedPose();
        m_poseHelper-&gt;ResetPose(GetNormalizedYaw(), m_modulePositions, frc::Pose2d{currentPose.X(), currentPose.Y(), pose.Rotation()});
    }
    else {
        m_poseHelper-&gt;ResetPose(GetNormalizedYaw(), m_modulePositions, pose);
    }
    //sets pose to current pose
    frc::SmartDashboard::PutNumber("Auto starting pose x", pose.X().value());
    frc::SmartDashboard::PutNumber("Auto starting pose y", pose.Y().value());
    frc::SmartDashboard::PutNumber("Auto starting pose rot", pose.Rotation().Degrees().value());
    // for (int i = 0; i &lt; 10; i++) {
    //     m_pigeon.SetYaw(pose.Rotation().Degrees());
    // }
}
</code></pre>
<p>Here is our full code repository: <a href="https://github.com/FIRSTTeam3189/Robot2025" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">GitHub - FIRSTTeam3189/Robot2025</a></p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":3,"updated_at":"2025-02-02T00:55:10.931Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":75,"reads":52,"readers_count":51,"score":385.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":484718,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-pose-setting-issues-erroneous-honomic-trajectories","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/FIRSTTeam3189/Robot2025","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - FIRSTTeam3189/Robot2025","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":65004,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-pose-setting-issues-erroneous-honomic-trajectories/484718/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true,"can_vote":false},{"id":3499526,"name":"","username":"Popcorn","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/popcorn/{size}/219298_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-02T00:43:08.549Z","cooked":"<p>In addition, our trajectories seem to be generated in non-holonomic mode even though the holonomic mode is checked in our GUI. Running a curved path shows the Pathplanner ghost/target robot rotating to face the direction of travel like a non-holonomic robot, instead of facing the set rotation.</p>
<p>This could explain the starting pose being set to the heading instead of our desired starting rotation.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":3,"updated_at":"2025-02-02T00:43:08.549Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":39,"readers_count":38,"score":22.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":484718,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-pose-setting-issues-erroneous-honomic-trajectories","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":65004,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-pose-setting-issues-erroneous-honomic-trajectories/484718/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3500068,"name":"","username":"Popcorn","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/popcorn/{size}/219298_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-02T19:33:53.656Z","cooked":"<p>We ended up finding two issues that created this problem:</p>
<ol>
<li>Our <code>PoseEstimator::GetEstimatedPose()</code> method was implemented incorrectly to fix a strange behavior in autonomous last year. Fixing this to use the estimator’s rotation instead of the gyro’s and updating <code>SwerveDrive::SetPose()</code> fixed this issue.</li>
<li>Pathplanner’s AutoBuilder somehow recognized our RobotConfig as non-holonomic, it seems. Switching our RobotConfig to be generated by <code>AutoBuilder::FromGUISettings()</code> fixed this issue, though we’re not sure why.</li>
